        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 6 at 6:57PM EDT until September 6 at 7:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 657 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Union, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Jonesville, Adamsburg, and Union.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.</instruction>
